CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1945, pg. 4, reads: "No Place To Go - Mrs. Roberta Slatton who took 'Squatters Rights' on a Library mining shack but never contacted the owners, Jones Incorporated, mining interests, handles her belongings while the Confer Brothers raze the house she occupies. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man working on partially razed home of Roberta Slatton, Library, Pennsylvania
